# Vistral Lab - Domain Boundaries Rules

## Domain Structure

### Domains

**Current domains:**
- `src/app/rentals/` - Rentals management domain (kanban, leads, property, team, notifications)
- `src/app/login/` - Authentication (shared)
- `src/app/api/` - API routes (shared backend)

### Domain Isolation Rule

**CRITICAL:** When working on a specific domain, do NOT touch other domains unless explicitly requested.

**Example:**
- Working on `src/app/rentals/leads/[id]/page.tsx`?
  - ✅ Modify `src/app/rentals/**` files
  - ✅ Use shared utilities from `src/lib/`
  - ✅ Use shared components from `src/components/ui/`
  - ✅ Modify `src/components/rentals/**` components
  - ❌ Do NOT modify `src/app/login/**` files

## Shared Resources

### What CAN be shared

**From `src/lib/`:**
- `lib/utils.ts` - Utility functions (cn, isDemoMode, etc.)
- `lib/constants.ts` - Constants and config
- `lib/supabase/**` - Supabase clients and types
- `lib/auth/**` - Auth providers and permissions
- `lib/config/**` - Configuration helpers
- `lib/i18n/**` - Translations

**From `src/components/ui/`:**
- All UI primitives (Button, Input, Form, Dialog, etc.)
- Shared layout components

**From `src/hooks/`:**
- Generic hooks
- Domain-specific hooks can be shared if appropriate

### What SHOULD be domain-specific

**Domain-specific components:**
- `src/components/rentals/**` - Rental domain components (kanban, lead cards, property views)
- `src/components/layout/**` - Navigation components
- `src/components/specs-card/**` - Specs card components

**Domain-specific hooks:**
- `src/hooks/use-leads.ts` - Leads data hook
- `src/hooks/use-lead.ts` - Single lead hook
- `src/hooks/use-property.ts` - Property data hook

## Cross-Domain Communication

**When domains need to interact:**

**Pattern 1: Shared Service via lib/**
```typescript
// src/lib/leads/lead-events.ts
export function getLeadEvents(leadId: string) { ... }
```

**Pattern 2: API Route**
```typescript
// src/app/api/leads/[leadId]/events/route.ts
// Both client and server code call this API
```

## Testing Expectations

When working within a domain:
- Test domain-specific functionality
- Verify shared resources still work
- Check no unintended side effects on other domains
